---
description: SQL and modeling guidance for analytical and warehouse-style work
globs: ["sql/**/*.sql", "docs/**/*.md"]
---

When working with SQL or data modeling in this repository:

- Prefer clear SQL over dense SQL.
- Use CTEs to improve readability when helpful.
- Name tables and columns so their intent is obvious.
- Be explicit about table grain.
- Separate raw, staging, and analytical layers when useful.
- Explain why a table is fact-like or dimension-like.
- Use PostgreSQL-friendly SQL unless there is a strong reason otherwise.

For transformation work:
- document assumptions
- note primary keys or uniqueness expectations
- mention data quality concerns
- keep business logic visible and easy to inspect
